article.headline: W. Michigan 70, Pepperdine 65
article.story: EUGENE, Ore. (AP) -- Joe Reitz had 14 points and 15 rebounds to lead Western Michigan to a 70-65 victory against Pepperdine at the World Vision International tournament on Sunday. Andre Ricks also scored 14 points for the Broncos (1-1), who hit seven free throws down the stretch to win the game. Daniel Johnson scored 15 points to pace the Waves (0-2). Pepperdine was up 64-63 with 1:15 to play when Reitz made two free throws to give the Broncos the lead for good. The score stayed the same until Reitz hit a free throw with 26 seconds left to make it a two-point game. Derek Fracalossi followed with two more free throws, and David Kool added two more with six seconds left to seal the win. Derek Drews scored 11 points and Martelle McLemore added 10 for the Broncos, who overcame 21 turnovers. Pepperdine shot 31 percent from the field and missed 31 of 38 3-point attempts. Reitz scored the first four points of the game and Drews added a 3-pointer as the Broncos got out to a 7-0 lead. A jumper by Drews with 1:16 left gave Western Michigan its largest lead of the first half, 34-22. The Broncos led 34-26 at the break. But the Waves got back in the game with a 12-4 run to open the second half.
